## {{headings.commonRules}}
- All work starts in plan mode
- Do not modify finalized specs without a CR (Change Request)
- All feedback must be scored on a 100-point scale (1-point increments) with specific deduction reasons
{{#if visualQa}}- Visual QA is performed at the designated Level (default: Level {{visualQaLevel}}){{/if}}
- Simplicity first — do not add features, abstractions, or error handling not explicitly requested
- Precise edits — change only what is requested, leave the rest untouched
- Workflow: Explore → Plan → Code → Commit (always in this order)
- Security: No hardcoded secrets, no `.env` commits, no dynamic code evaluation
- Parallel processing: Read independent files in parallel, run independent searches concurrently
- SSOT: Official Claude Code documentation is the single source of truth — when in doubt, verify with `sync-spec` skill

