## Context Engineering

Context is a scarce resource. See `context-engineering` skill for detailed guidelines.

### Progressive Disclosure (L1 → L2 → L3)
- **L1 Metadata**: CLAUDE.md, agent frontmatter — always loaded
- **L2 Module**: Skills, ADRs, specs — loaded on demand per Agent Context Rules table
- **L3 Data**: Tool outputs, file contents — loaded just-in-time, offload results to `.claude/context/scratch-pad.md`

### Key Principles
- Every token has an opportunity cost — prefer targeted reads over full-file reads
- Forward original content between agents — never paraphrase (Telephone Game prevention)
- Append decisions to `.claude/context/decisions.jsonl` for session continuity
- Use `.claude/context/mailbox/` for async inter-agent messages

## {{headings.failureModes}}

### {{headings.detectionCriteria}}
- Score below 60: Immediate failure declaration
- Score 60-69: One revision opportunity, failure if below 70 on re-score

### {{headings.escalationRules}}
- 2 consecutive failures on same task: Orchestrator escalates to Human

